description: {"blocks":[{"key":"2cf59","text":"This protocols is part of the ANU Biosecurity mini-research project #1 \"Plant Pathogen Diagnostics: Visuals, subcultures, and genomics\". ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8bpag","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ccitv","text":"You will be provided four pots of 3-4 week old wheat plants that have been infected with different wheat pathogens. Each pot has been infected with one major pathogen. You will not know which pot has been infected with which pathogen. However, you will be provided a compendium of 10-15 wheat pathogens that will guide you to identify the infective agent for each treatment group. The fifth treatment group will be uninfected wheat plants which will be clearly identified. You can use treatment group #5 as negative control for your experiments.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"37m61","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"98hpk","text":"In total, each group will obtain five pots each:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dfmgd","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f7abe","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"1fvs9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8152l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b9o6b","text":"This specific protocol is a step by step guide to capture and describe to the disease symptoms the provided wheat plants display in week 2 and 3. You can then compare the observed disease symptoms with the provided compendium and other online sources to try to identify the causal infective agent.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2gn4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9bd98","text":"The final goal is to achieve the following:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"163fl","text":"obtain high quality images of your diseased leaves for each treatment group that are representative. These pictures can be taken with your mobile phone for the complete attached leaves lined up on black cardboard paper or via the stereo microscope as demonstrated by the support staff.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"15dug","text":"provide a detailed description of the symptoms observed on the leaves. This includes the following: size, shape, form, color, microscopic structure, spore shape and color, and timing of disease symptom development post infection.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"21g3d","text":"Compare your observed disease symptoms with the uninfected negative control, the provided compendium, and online sources.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aqvsm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2s2of","text":"This protocol is applicable for week 2 and 3. steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"175d4","text":"You will receive five pots with wheat plants as detailed in the \"Description\" section. Please label each pot with your research group name, the date, and the treatment group. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"73so3","text":"Carefully, study the plants in each pot. Select four to five leaves for each treatment group that show representative symptoms [TG#1-4] or not in the case of the negative control [TG#5].","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ago35","text":"Perform the following steps [3.1 to 3.11 and 4] for each treatment group [#1-5].","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8j1rh","text":"Obtain one black cardboard paper. Label it with your research group name, the date, and the treatment group.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"49qkn","text":"Layout your cardboard paper horizontally in front of you. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6ius1","text":"Mark the bottom side closest to you of your black cardboard paper with a horizontal line approximately 1-2 cm from the edge. Make this line parallel to the edge. This will be called the baseline.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fev41","text":"For your selected treatment group, cut the selected leaves at the base.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fm10f","text":"Line up your cut leaves with the leaf apex pointing away from the baseline and the leaf base aligned to the baseline. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8atqp","text":"Mark the position of the apex with a pen. This mark is called the apex-mark.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4m88s","text":"Attach one strip of double-sided tape at the bottom baseline. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4i4ff","text":"Attach one strip of double-sided tape parallel to the bottom baseline at a distance about 1cm below the apex mark. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ev0c9","text":"Attach your cut leaves to the cardboard with the leave base affixed to the lower baseline double-sided tape and the apex affixed to the double-sided tape close to the apex-mark.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f27uo","text":"Place a ruler next to your leaves and take a clear picture with a camera. Having clear labels and a ruler will allow you to clearly identify the specific sample later on and add a scale bar to the picture digitally if required. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aiuu","text":"Cut your selected leaves for the treatment group you are currently working on.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1ika","text":"In addition, you can also take pictures of the disease symptoms with the stereo microscope. Please see a demonstrate for hands on instructions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bcb2p","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"99q7q","text":"Make sure to label your pictures as follows so we can share them online after class and you can clearly identify your pictures. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7ehfm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1bo8s","text":"YYYYMMDD_ResearchGroupName_TreatmentGroupNumber_PictureNumber","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8fgch","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"v31h","text":"For example:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8rgtk","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2njoa","text":"20230206_BSPS_TG1_2.jpg","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"11b6k","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6vi6i","text":"Pictures that do not follow this naming convention will not be shared with the class.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"eq0d3","text":"Repeat all steps for each treatment group in week 2 and week 3.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
